From bad679c61448009434c5d4f42e80b2bd00cd088c Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Chronium <chronium@interlink.local>
Date: Mon, 8 Jun 2026 19:04:48 +0700
Subject: [PATCH] chronium: per-profile WebAuthn UVPA + WebGL
 getSupportedExtensions() spoof

Adds two ShardX-equivalent fingerprint vectors that anti-detect tooling
at the bank/exchange tier specifically interrogates:

PublicKeyCredential.isUserVerifyingPlatformAuthenticatorAvailable()
  Returns true on real consumer devices with Windows Hello / Touch ID
  configured, false otherwise. Spoofing it to 'true' for a macOS-claiming
  profile, 'false' for a generic Linux box keeps the platform-auth bit
  coherent with the rest of the surface. Without this, sites like
  ShardX/Binance and the WebAuthn-gated grok.com sign-in see the mojom
  default (real machine state) and treat the session as inconsistent.

WebGLRenderingContextBase::getSupportedExtensions()
  ANGLE on Windows surfaces a markedly different set of GL extensions
  than Metal on macOS or Vulkan on Linux. Profiles that claim
  'ANGLE Metal Renderer: Apple M1' but expose
  ANGLE_provoking_vertex_compatibility (a D3D11 extension) fail
  pixelscan's GPU cross-check. Returning the canned per-profile list
  keeps the extension surface aligned with the spoofed
  UNMASKED_RENDERER string.

Plumbing follows the same shape as 0015:
- FingerprintState gains uvpa bool + WebGL extension list parser
- Two new switches (kFingerprintWebAuthnUvpa, kFingerprintWebGLExtensions)
  appended by the browser client; extensions list is hex-encoded over
  the CLI because joined names span argv whitespace boundaries.
- chrome_content_renderer_client routes them into FingerprintState
  during RenderThreadStarted.
- public_key_credential.cc resolves the promise from the override
  immediately when set, skipping the authenticator mojom round-trip.
- webgl_rendering_context_base.cc returns the canned list directly
  from getSupportedExtensions when active.

Profile schema additions (now also generated by
scripts/convert-shardx-profiles.py from the 170 ShardX device JSONs):
  webauthn.uvpa: true|false
  webgl.extensions: ["EXT_color_buffer_float", ...]
